result.name: The effect of local extinction and recolonization on nuclear relative to mitochondrial population structure with an application to multi-genomic SNP variation in the red flour beetle, Tribolium castaneum
result.description: Analysis of variation in Tribolium castaneum mitochondrial genome including: (1) Comparison with nuclear FST, (2) Theory on colonization by multiply mated females, (3) Evidence of a maintained mitochondrial polymorphism in two of the study populations.
